    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n      <strong>School:</strong>&nbsp;conjuration&nbsp;(creation)&nbsp;[force];\n    <br>\n    <strong>Level:</strong>&nbsp;Wizard 1;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    <br>\n    <strong>Components:</strong>&nbsp;V, S, F (a piece of cured leather)<br>\n    \n      <strong>Casting Time:</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Range:</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Target:</strong>&nbsp;creature touched<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration:</strong>&nbsp;1 hour/level (D)<br>\n    \n        <strong>Saving Throw:</strong>&nbsp;Will negates (harmless)\n        <br>\n        <strong>Spell Resistance:</strong>&nbsp;no<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  \n\n\n<p>\nAn invisible but tangible field of force surrounds the subject of a <i>mage armor </i>spell, providing a +4 armor bonus to AC.\n</p><p>Unlike mundane armor, <i>mage armor </i>entails no armor check penalty, arcane spell failure chance, or speed reduction. Since <i>mage armor </i>is made of force, incorporeal creatures can’t bypass it the way they do normal armor.\n</p><p><i>Focus: </i>A piece of cured leather.\n</p>\n<hr/>\n\n\n\n</div>\n",
